{
  "info": {
    "name": "hobby-track API",
    "description": "End-to-end test collection for the hobby-track backend.\n\n## Setup\n\n1. Start the API: `pnpm --filter @hobby-track/api dev`\n2. (Optional) Reset DB to clean state: `pnpm --filter @hobby-track/api db:reset-dev`\n3. In Postman, ensure cookies are managed automatically (Settings → General → Automatically follow redirects: ON; cookie jar is on by default).\n4. Run requests in order — `Login` sets a cookie that all subsequent requests reuse.\n\n## Variables\n\n- `baseUrl` — defaults to `http://localhost:3000`\n- `password` — defaults to `changeme-dev-only` (change to match your `APP_PASSWORD`)\n- `itemId`, `bookId`, `wishlistBookId` — captured automatically by tests in earlier requests\n\n## Folders\n\n- **0. Auth** — login / me / logout\n- **1. Items — Create & Read** — basic CRUD reads\n- **2. Items — List Filters** — `?type`, `?status`, `?search`, `?sort`, pagination\n- **3. Items — Update & Side Effects** — verifies `lastTouchedAt`, `startedAt`, `completedAt` auto-set\n- **4. Active Limit (book limit=2)** — 409 + `?force=true` override on POST and PATCH\n- **5. Settings** — GET / PATCH / validation\n- **6. Delete** — 204 + 404 on second delete\n- **7. Auth Enforcement** — clear cookies in Postman first, then run\n\nMost requests have a `Tests` tab that asserts status code and (where useful) body shape — run with the Collection Runner to see pass/fail across the suite.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:3000", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "password", "value": "changeme-dev-only", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "itemId", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "bookId", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "wishlistBookId", "value": "", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "0. Auth",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login (sets cookie)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('returns ok:true', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.eql({ ok: true }));",
                  "pm.test('sets auth_token cookie', () => pm.expect(pm.cookies.has('auth_token')).to.be.true);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "auth", "login"] },
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"password\": \"{{password}}\"\n}" }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Me (check authenticated)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('authenticated:true', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.eql({ authenticated: true }));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/me", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "auth", "me"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Logout",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": ["pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/logout", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "auth", "logout"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Login again (after logout test)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": ["pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "auth", "login"] },
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"password\": \"{{password}}\"\n}" }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
